  "summary": "Apache APISIX: Cas-auth plugin open redirect via unsanitized cookie value",
  "details": "URL Redirection to Untrusted Site ('Open Redirect') vulnerability in Apache APISIX.\n\nThe default configuration of cas-auth in Apache APISIX is vulnerable to phishing and credential theft.\n\nThis issue affects Apache APISIX: from 3.0.0 through 3.16.0.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 3.17.0, which fixes the issue.",
